00:16:59,324 --> 00:17:03,693
你以为凭这份拙劣的东西
便可以分析我？
You think you can dissect
me with this blunt little tool?

161
00:17:04,496 --> 00:17:07,294
不是！我相信你的学识...
No! l thought
that your knowledge--

162
00:17:07,499 --> 00:17:09,797
你很有野心，是不是？
You're so ambitious, aren't you?

163
00:17:10,268 --> 00:17:13,795
可知道你拿着那个高级皮包
和穿着廉价鞋子像个什么？
You know what you look like, with
your good bag and your cheap shoes?

164
00:17:14,005 --> 00:17:15,438
像个土包子
You look like a rube.

165
00:17:16,107 --> 00:17:20,237
一个干净、忙碌
带点品味的土包子
A well-scrubbed, hustling rube
with a little taste.

166
00:17:21,045 --> 00:17:23,275
虽然你衣食无忧地成长...
Nutrition has given you
some length of bone...

167
00:17:23,481 --> 00:17:26,644
你不外乎是个白种低下层的人
...but you're not more than one
generation from white trash...

168
00:17:26,851 --> 00:17:28,682
是不是，史达琳探员？
...are you, Agent Starling?

169
00:17:28,887 --> 00:17:31,685
你极力想摆脱口音...
The accent you've tried
so desperately to shed...

170
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:33,949
地道的西维吉尼亚州腔调
...pure West Virginia.

171
00:17:34,159 --> 00:17:36,218
你父亲是个矿工吗？
ls your father a coal miner?

172
00:17:36,428 --> 00:17:38,157
那盏灯可有令他满身臭气？
Does he stink of the lamp?

173
00:17:38,496 --> 00:17:43,229
我知道那些男孩怎样迅速搭上你
在汽车后座里乱摸
l know how quickly the boys found you,
all those tedious, sticky fumblings...

174
00:17:43,435 --> 00:17:46,871
你却想着走出去
...in the back seats of cars,
while you dreamed of getting out.

175
00:17:47,071 --> 00:17:48,436
走去天涯海角
Getting anywhere.

176
00:17:48,706 --> 00:17:52,267
直走到联邦调查局
Getting all the way to the FBl.

177
00:17:55,580 --> 00:17:58,378
你很有观察力
You see a lot, doctor.

178
00:17:58,583 --> 00:18:01,051
但你能否用你敏锐的观察力...
But are you strong enough
to point that...

179
00:18:01,252 --> 00:18:03,777
来分析自己？
...high-powered
perception at yourself?

180
00:18:04,789 --> 00:18:05,915
怎么样？
What about it?

181
00:18:06,124 --> 00:18:10,288
不如你探究一下自己
把观察所得写下来
Why don't you look at yourself
and write down what you see?

182
00:18:10,495 --> 00:18:12,224
或者你害怕这样做吧
Or maybe you're afraid to.

183
00:18:22,006 --> 00:18:24,873
曾经有一个人口调查员想测试我
A census taker once tried to test me.

184
00:18:25,076 --> 00:18:28,409
我把他的肝配蚕豆吃了
l ate his liver
with some fava beans...

185
00:18:28,613 --> 00:18:30,911
还有美味的红酒呢
...and a nice Chianti.

186
00:18:39,724 --> 00:18:42,090
小史达琳，你飞回学校去吧
You fly back to school now,
little Starling.

187
00:18:42,994 --> 00:18:44,484
飞吧...
Fly, fly, fly.

188
00:18:59,477 --> 00:19:01,377
我咬我的手腕...
l bit my wrist...

189
00:19:01,613 --> 00:19:05,049
让我可以死掉
...so l could die.

190
00:19:05,049 --> 00:19:06,311
看这些血
Look at the blood!

191
00:19:07,251 --> 00:19:08,650
吓到你了
Gotcha.

192
00:19:09,053 --> 00:19:11,146
迈克斯！你这个混蛋！
Miggs! You stupid fuck!

193
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:19,528
史达琳探员！回来！史达琳探员
Agent Starling! Come back!
Agent Starling! Agent Starling!

194
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:22,824
我不会让那种事情再发生
我讨厌不礼貌的
l would not have had that happen.
Discourtesy is ugly to me.

195
00:19:23,034 --> 00:19:25,468
-那么做这个测验吧
-不做，但我会令你开心的
-Then do this test!
-No, but l will make you happy.

196
00:19:25,670 --> 00:19:28,195
-我会给你一个大好机会
-什么？
-l'll give you a chance at your love.
-What?

197
00:19:28,406 --> 00:19:33,173
升职，听着
你自我反省一下，克丽丝史达琳
Advancement. Listen. Look deep
within yourself, Clarice Starling.

198
00:19:33,377 --> 00:19:37,575
找出我从前的病人莫菲小姐
Go seek out Miss Mofet,
an old patient of mine. M-O-F-E-T.

199
00:19:37,882 --> 00:19:40,407
我相信迈克斯不会这么快发作的...
l don't think Miggs could
manage again so soon...

200
00:19:40,618 --> 00:19:42,848
虽然他是疯的，快去
...even though he is crazy.
Go now!

201
00:20:24,362 --> 00:20:25,556
你好，比尔
Hi, Bill.

202
00:20:30,334 --> 00:20:32,063
-爸爸
-克丽丝
-Daddy!
-Hey, Clarice.

203
00:20:36,307 --> 00:20:39,834
-爸爸，你有没有抓到坏人？
-没有，他们跑掉了
-Did you get any bad guys, Daddy?
-No, angel. They all got away.

204
00:20:40,044 --> 00:20:41,534
该死
Ah, shoot.

205
00:21:01,899 --> 00:21:04,163
联邦调查局，举手，别动！
FBl! Hands up! Don't move!

206
00:21:04,368 --> 00:21:07,895
转过身来，把双手放在后面
好的
Turn around. Hands behind your back.
Thumbs up.

207
00:21:11,909 --> 00:21:13,706
史达琳，你已经死了
You're dead, Starling.

208
00:21:14,245 --> 00:21:18,375
强生，进入和指挥都做得很好
史达琳，你哪里有危险？
Johnson, good entry, good command.
Starling, where's your danger area?

209
00:21:18,582 --> 00:21:19,981
-在角落
-你有没有检查过它？
-ln the corner.
-Did you check it?

210
00:21:20,184 --> 00:21:21,776
-没有，长官
-所以你已经死了
-No, sir.
-That's why you're dead.

211
00:21:22,086 --> 00:21:25,112
3109？
3-1 -0-9?

212
00:21:25,323 --> 00:21:29,760
打破门或窗闯入或者撤退
Breaking doors or windows
to enter or exit.

213
00:21:30,728 --> 00:21:31,990
404号规条呢？
Rule 404?

214
00:21:35,132 --> 00:21:36,861
（巴尔的摩心理医生
获得最高荣誉）

215
00:21:38,402 --> 00:21:40,461
（著名心理医生被控谋杀）

216
00:21:45,876 --> 00:21:47,776
（食人狂魔审讯带来新的恐怖）

217
00:21:50,848 --> 00:21:53,180
克丽丝，你的电话，是教官
Clarice, phone. lt's the guru.

218
00:21:53,384 --> 00:21:55,011
克劳福？谢谢，雅戴
Crawford? Thanks, Ardelia.

219
00:21:55,486 --> 00:21:57,920
-史达琳？
-长官
-Starling?
-Sir.

220
00:21:58,122 --> 00:21:59,555
迈克斯死了
Miggs is dead.

221
00:22:00,725 --> 00:22:01,714
死了？
Dead?

222
00:22:02,593 --> 00:22:03,821
怎会的？
How?

223
00:22:04,562 --> 00:22:07,622
守卫听到汉内堡莱达
下午时对他低声说话
The orderly heard Lecter whispering
to him all afternoon.

224
00:22:07,832 --> 00:22:10,426
他们在夜间巡查时
发现他吞掉自己的舌头
They found him at bed check.
He'd swallowed his tongue.

225
00:22:13,471 --> 00:22:14,563
史达琳？
Starling?

226
00:22:15,106 --> 00:22:18,132
我还在听，我只是...
Yeah. l'm still here, sir. l just--

227
00:22:18,342 --> 00:22:20,071
我不知道对这件事该有何感想
l don't know how to feel about this.

228
00:22:20,644 --> 00:22:24,080
你不用感想什么
莱达这样做只是为了自娱
You don't have to feel any way.
Lecter did it to amuse himself.

229
00:22:25,416 --> 00:22:27,350
我明白今天很难受
Look, l know it got ugly today...

230
00:22:27,885 --> 00:22:32,219
但你提到莫菲，有后续行动吗？
...but you mentioned a name,
''Mofet.'' Any follow-up on her?

231
00:22:33,858 --> 00:22:37,021
他在被捕前
把大部分病人的病历销毁了
He destroyed most of his patients'
histories prior to capture...

232
00:22:37,228 --> 00:22:40,720
所以没有莫菲的记录
...so there's no record
of anyone named Mofet.

233
00:22:40,931 --> 00:22:45,027
我觉得“你自己”这个参考资料
对莱达来说太造作了
But l thought the ''yourself' reference
was too hokey for Lecter...

234
00:22:45,236 --> 00:22:49,400
我想起他是来自巴尔的摩
便翻查电话簿
...so l figured he's from Baltimore,
and l looked in the phone book.

235
00:22:49,607 --> 00:22:52,872
那里有一间叫“你自己”的
自助式仓库
And there's a
''Your Self' storage facility...

236
00:22:53,077 --> 00:22:55,568
在巴尔的摩市外围
...right outside
of downtown Baltimore, sir.

237
00:22:57,782 --> 00:23:00,012
31号仓已经租了十年...
Unit 31 was leased...

238
00:23:00,217 --> 00:23:03,482
租金是全数预缴的
...for 1 0 years, prepaid in full.

239
00:23:03,687 --> 00:23:05,621
合约是以一个...
The contract was in the name...

240
00:23:05,823 --> 00:23:09,589
是莫菲赫斯达小姐的人定的
...of a Miss Hester Mofet.

241
00:23:09,794 --> 00:23:12,422
自从1980年就没有人来过了？
So nobody's been
in here since 1 980?

242
00:23:12,630 --> 00:23:14,427
以我所知是没有
Not to my knowledge.

243
00:23:14,999 --> 00:23:18,765
我的顾客都很重视私隐权的
Privacy is a great concern
to my customers.

244
00:23:19,503 --> 00:23:21,596
对，我答应不会扰乱任何东西
Yes, l won't disturb anything,
l promise.

245
00:23:21,806 --> 00:23:23,831
我很快便会离开
l'll be out of here
before you know it.

246
00:23:24,375 --> 00:23:26,673
-要帮忙吗？
-好的
-May l help you?
-Yes, actually.

247
00:23:27,044 --> 00:23:28,033
这里
Here.

248
00:23:32,983 --> 00:23:36,578
-它被卡着
-明天可以叫我的儿子来
-lt's stuck.
-We could return tomorrow with my son.

249
00:23:37,388 --> 00:23:38,878
他怎么样？
What about him?

250
00:23:40,291 --> 00:23:45,228
我本可叫我的司机帮你
但他讨厌体力劳动
l would ask my driver to help you,
but he detests physical labor.

251
00:23:45,896 --> 00:23:46,954
是吧
Right.

252
00:23:47,665 --> 00:23:50,293
你别走开，我很快回来
You stay here.
l'll be back in one minute.

253
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:25,527
它被卡着，请你把那支电筒给我
lt's stuck. Will you hand me
that flashlight?

254
00:24:39,917 --> 00:24:42,715
如果这道门跌下来...
lf this door should fall down...

255
00:24:43,254 --> 00:24:45,688
或者有什么意外...
...or anything else...

256
00:24:45,890 --> 00:24:48,154
这是我们巴尔的摩办公室的
电话号码
...this is the number
for our Baltimore office.

257
00:24:48,692 --> 00:24:50,319
他们知道你跟我在一起的
They know that you're with me.

258
00:24:50,628 --> 00:24:54,223
-如果有意外就找他们吧
-好的，史达琳小姐
-Call them if anything should happen.
-Yes, Miss Starling.

259
00:27:25,515 --> 00:27:28,040
克丽丝，他们在等你
Clarice. Here, they're waiting
for you.

260
00:27:28,251 --> 00:27:29,775
小心
Watch your step.

261
00:27:30,987 --> 00:27:35,014
“莫菲赫斯达”是拼字猜谜吧？
Hester Mofet. lt's an anagram,
isn't it, doctor?

262
00:27:35,225 --> 00:27:38,217
意思是“我其余的东西”
Hester Mofet: ''The rest of me''?

263
00:27:38,628 --> 00:27:42,564
那表示车库是你租的？
''Miss The Rest Of Me,'' meaning
that you rented that garage?

264
00:28:18,402 --> 00:28:19,426
谢谢
Thank you.

265
00:28:20,637 --> 00:28:21,968
你止血了
Your bleeding has stopped.

266
00:28:24,474 --> 00:28:25,634
怎么...？
How did...?

267
00:28:27,644 --> 00:28:28,668
没有大碍的
lt's nothing.

268
00:28:29,446 --> 00:28:30,879
只是皮外伤
lt's just a scratch.

269
00:28:32,482 --> 00:28:34,746
莱达医生，那瓶里的头颅是谁的？
Dr. Lecter, whose head
is in that bottle?

270
00:28:34,951 --> 00:28:38,079
为什么你不问我
关于水牛比尔的事？
Why don't you ask me
about Buffalo Bill?

271
00:28:38,355 --> 00:28:39,982
你知道他的事？
Do you know something about him?

272
00:28:40,223 --> 00:28:43,920
如果我看过档案可能知道的
你可以替我拿
l might if l saw the case file.
You could get that for me.

273
00:28:44,494 --> 00:28:47,463
谈谈莫菲小姐吧
你要我去找他
Let's talk about Miss Mofet.
You wanted me to find him.

274
00:28:48,598 --> 00:28:53,592
他的真名是班哲文赖普
是我的前病患
His real name is Benjamin Raspail.
A former patient of mine...

275
00:28:54,171 --> 00:28:58,733
他的恋爱对象，有点怪异
...whose romantic attachments
ran to, shall we say, the exotic.

276
00:28:59,309 --> 00:29:03,541
我没有杀他，只是把他藏起来
就像我发现他时的样子
l did not kill him, merely tucked
him away, very much as l found him...

277
00:29:03,747 --> 00:29:06,113
在他错过了三次约会之后
...after he'd missed
three appointments.

278
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:09,409
若你没有杀他，那么是谁杀？
lf you didn't kill him, who did?

279
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:12,721
谁知道？对他来说是件好事
Who can say?
Best thing for him, really.

280
00:29:12,923 --> 00:29:15,323
他的治疗没有功效
His therapy was going nowhere.

281
00:29:15,826 --> 00:29:18,920
他的裙子、化妆...
His dress, makeup....

282
00:29:19,362 --> 00:29:20,954
赖普是个异性装扮癖好者？
Raspail was a transvestite?

283
00:29:21,164 --> 00:29:25,828
生活上？不是
只是普通的躁狂抑郁
ln life? Oh, no.
Garden variety manic-depressive.

284
00:29:26,036 --> 00:29:28,504
乏味，非常乏味
Tedious, very tedious.

285
00:29:28,705 --> 00:29:31,105
现在我把他看成是一个实验
l now think of him as an experiment.

286
00:29:31,341 --> 00:29:34,833
一个没经验的杀手尝试转变
A fledgling killer's first effort
at transformation.

287
00:29:35,045 --> 00:29:37,843
你看到他时有何感觉？
How did you feel when you saw him,
Clarice?

288
00:29:38,215 --> 00:29:40,149
初时很害怕，后来...
Scared at first, then...

289
00:29:41,218 --> 00:29:42,515
便很振奋
...exhilarated.

290
00:29:43,153 --> 00:29:45,348
克劳福在提拔你，是吗？
Jack Crawford is helping your career,
isn't he?

291
00:29:45,555 --> 00:29:48,285
看来你们互相倾慕呢
Apparently, he likes you
and you like him too.

292
00:29:49,059 --> 00:29:50,754
我从没有想过
l never thought about it.

293
00:29:51,328 --> 00:29:53,956
你认为克劳福对你有遐想吗？
Do you think Jack Crawford
wants you, sexually?

294
00:29:54,164 --> 00:29:59,295
他年纪大很多
你对他可有想入非非？
He is much older, but do you think
he visualizes scenarios, exchanges?

295
00:29:59,503 --> 00:30:00,663
跟你做爱？
Fucking you?

296
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:08,837
我没有兴趣
这是迈克斯会说的那种话
That doesn't interest me. lt's the
sort of thing that Miggs would say.

297
00:30:10,881 --> 00:30:12,405
不再是了
Not anymore.

298
00:30:20,023 --> 00:30:21,650
谢谢你，巴尼
Thank you, Barney.

299
00:30:25,562 --> 00:30:27,553
你的画呢？
What happened to your drawings?

300
00:30:29,199 --> 00:30:33,568
惩罚，为了迈克斯那件事
像那个传道节目...
Punishment, you see, for Miggs.
Just like that gospel program.

301
00:30:33,904 --> 00:30:36,668
你离开后他们就会调高声音
When you leave, they'll turn
the volume way up.

302
00:30:37,007 --> 00:30:40,170
奇顿医生喜欢这些折磨伎俩
Dr. Chilton does enjoy
his petty torments.

303
00:30:40,977 --> 00:30:43,207
你说转变是什么意思？
What did you mean
by ''transformation,'' doctor?

304
00:30:52,355 --> 00:30:55,722
克丽丝，我在这里八年了
l've been in this room
for eight years now, Clarice.

305
00:30:56,059 --> 00:30:59,460
我知道在我有生之年
他们都不会释放我
l know they will never
ever let me out while l'm alive.

306
00:31:00,297 --> 00:31:02,424
我想要的是一个景观
What l want is a view.

307
00:31:02,632 --> 00:31:06,432
我想要一个看到树和水的窗户
l want a window where l can see a tree
or even water.

308
00:31:06,636 --> 00:31:10,265
我想去一间远离
奇顿医生的联邦监狱
l want to be in a federal institution
far away from Dr. Chilton.

309
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:12,839
你说“没经验的杀手”
是什么意思？
What did you mean
by ''fledgling killer''?

310
00:31:13,043 --> 00:31:14,874
你是否说他已经再次杀人？
Are you saying he's killed again?

311
00:31:15,178 --> 00:31:18,375
我根据案件的证据
给你对水牛比尔...
l'm offering you a psychological
profile on Buffalo Bill...

312
00:31:18,582 --> 00:31:20,675
作心理分析
...based on the case evidence.

313
00:31:26,056 --> 00:31:35,197
我会帮你抓到他的
l'll help you catch him, Clarice.

314
00:31:35,197 --> 00:31:37,256
你知道他是谁，是不是？
You know who he is, don't you?

315
00:31:38,133 --> 00:31:40,863
告诉我谁把你的病人斩首了
Tell me who decapitated
your patient, doctor.

316
00:31:41,069 --> 00:31:43,867
愿意等待的人都有好报的
All good things to those who wait.

317
00:31:44,339 --> 00:31:48,435
我已经等了
但杰克能等多久？
l've waited, Clarice. But how long
can you and old Jackie-boy wait?

318
00:31:49,011 --> 00:31:54,176
我们的小比尔一定正在找寻着
下一位特别的女士了
Our little Billy must already be
searching for that next special lady.

319
00:31:57,953 --> 00:32:01,787
（田纳西州孟斐斯市）

320
